      "writtenOn": "2020-10-30T20:28:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m don\u0027t follow the \"can\u0027t be checked\" assertion, can you clarify?. \n\nThat bit field is always initialized to 0 in the constructor. I can make it private to enforce no one able to modify it. There\u0027s a static_assert that the Metadata size is 32 bits, so if that passes, we know there are no other unassigned bits that could be undefined and break comparison. I can also update asBitmask() to assert that fUnused remains 0.",
      "parentUuid": "22e56d24_7a412f3f",
